problem_question: A train leaves a station at 72 km/h. Two hours later, a faster train leaves the same station at 88.4 km/h. How long after the faster train departs will it overtake the slower one?
full_response:
<answer1>
Let me solve this step by step.

When the faster train starts, the slower train has already traveled for 2 hours at 72 km/h.
Distance covered by slower train = 72 × 2 = 144 km

Let t = time (in hours) after the faster train departs when it overtakes the slower train.

At the moment of overtaking:
- Distance traveled by faster train = 88.4t km
- Distance traveled by slower train = 144 + 72t km (initial 144 km plus additional distance)

Setting them equal:
88.4t = 144 + 72t
88.4t - 72t = 144
16.4t = 144
t = 144/16.4
t = 8.78048780487804878048780487804878048780487804878049

8.78048780487804878048780487804878048780487804878049
</answer1>
